m school or had poor educational results. Low achievement is a misfortune for the individuals concerned and a considerable social problem. The costs to society of not addressi\nng the issues discussed here are high\n.”\nSeptember 2013\nReferences \nIqbal\n K (2000). \nConsultations with Black and Minority Ethnic Voluntary Organisations about the New Connexions Service \nHome Office a\nnd \nDfEE\n; \nIqbal\n K (2009): \nEquality and diversity issues within Family Intervention Projects – some observations on advice in publications, and from Key Workers\n \nDfE\n \nIqbal\n K (2013). \nDear Birmingham – a conversation with My Hometown \nXlibris\n Publishing\n \nIqbal\n K (2005). \nUnderachievement of White Disadvantaged Pupils in Birmingham\n \n Overview and Scrutiny Committee (2013). \nExamination and Assessment Results 2013 \nBirmingham City Council\n \nCassen\n R and \nKingdon\n G (2007). \nTackling low educational achievement \nJ\noseph \nRowntree\n Foundation\n \nStrand, S. &amp; Winston, J. (2008).\n \nEducational aspirations in inner city schools.\n  \nEducational Studies, 34, (4), 249-267.\n Ofsted (2000). \nImproving City Schools\n DCSF (2009). \nDeprivation and Education \n \nMaylor\n U et al (2007). \nDiversity and Citizenship in the Curriculum: Research Review\n DFES\n \nIqbal\n K (2010). \nWhite working class underachievement- a case for Positive Action\n, Forward Partnership\n \nDesforges\n  C, \nAbouchaar\n A (2003). \nThe Impact of Parental Involvement, Parental Suppo\nrt and Family Education on Pupil Achievement and Adjustment: A Literature Review \nDFES\n \n \nIqbal\n K (2010). \nWhite working class needs the minority treatment \nTimes Educational Supplement 5 November  \n \n \nIqbal\n K (2012). \nAddressing white working class underachie\nvement – \nits\n not rocket science \nAmazon Kindle\n \nCassen\n R and \nKingdon\n G (2007). \nTackling low educational achievement \nJoseph \nRowntree\n Foundation\n"